dc_title_s: Sioux County, Iowa, 1956, aerial photomosaic index
dc_description_s: Title supplied by cataloger based on information from sheet labels. Images are photoreductions of mosaics created from original aerial photographs. Designating symbol BKS. Form of individual image numbering: BKS-2R-[number], BKS-3R-[number], BKS-4R-[number], or BKS-5R-[number]."Flying completed 11-8-56" Flown by Puckett aerial Surveys, Inc. Louisville, Kentucky."Approximate scale, 1:20,000" [refers to individual images from which mosaic was made].|Contact the Map Collection at The University of Iowa Libraries: http://www.lib.uiowa.edu/maps/contact/
